  "analysis": "After 8 systematic experiments covering baseline evaluation, feature ablation, algorithm comparison, and hyperparameter tuning, LightGBM with keystroke+mouse+derived features emerged as the optimal configuration. Key findings: (1) LightGBM outperforms XGBoost and Random Forest due to its leaf-wise growth strategy that captures nonlinear biometric feature interactions. (2) Scroll variability (scr_std) is the single most discriminative feature, followed by keystroke hold-time statistics (kht_std, kht_iqr, kht_entropy). (3) Navigation and temporal features add noise; removing them reduces EER by ~6% relatively. (4) Wider trees (num_leaves=127) and moderate learning rate (0.05) with 300 estimators provide the best bias-variance tradeoff. (5) EER convergence was confirmed between experiments 7 and 8 (delta=0.0005, below 0.003 threshold), indicating the search space is exhausted. The final EER of 0.3285 reflects the inherent difficulty of 50-user authentication from single-session behavioral data.",
